.TH WHITEROSE 1 "2026-07-13" "1.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
whiterose \- git-aware safety shell for developers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B whiterose
[\fI\-\-help\fR | \fI\-\-version\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBwhiterose\fR is an interactive shell that wraps git with safety
interceptors. It runs inside a git repository and provides:
.IP \(bu 3
Force\-push protection against remote\-ahead commits
.IP \(bu 3
Automatic upstream setup on bare \fBpush\fR
.IP \(bu 3
Smart \fBpull\fR (rebase on clean tree, merge if dirty)
.IP \(bu 3
Color\-coded \fBstatus\fR reformat
.IP \(bu 3
Automatic backups before destructive commands (reset \-\-hard,
checkout \-\-, clean \-f*, force push, rebase, branch \-d/\-D,
stash drop/clear, rm, tag \-d, commit \-\-amend)
.IP \(bu 3
\fBundo\fR command to restore the most recent backup
.IP \(bu 3
\fBbackups\fR command to list all saved backups
.IP \(bu 3
\fBconfig reload\fR to re\-read .whiterose.toml without restart
.IP \(bu 3
Merge conflict display and lockfile auto\-fix
.IP \(bu 3
Commit guard (blocks commit when conflicts remain or message is empty)
.IP \(bu 3
Protected branch confirmation
.IP \(bu 3
Clean preview (shows what \-f will delete before running)
.IP \(bu 3
Reset preview (shows how many commits will be discarded)
.IP \(bu 3
Pretty \fBlog\fR, \fBdiff\fR, \fBshow\fR, \fBreflog\fR formatting
.IP \(bu 3
Novice mode with plain\-language explanations
.IP \(bu 3
Beginner aliases: new\-branch, switch, save, sync, share
.IP \(bu 3
History persistence across restarts (~/.whiterose_history)
.IP \(bu 3
Ctrl\-C passthrough (doesn't kill whiterose, only the child)
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\fB\-\-help\fR, \fB\-h\fR
Display help text and exit.
.TP
\fB\-\-version\fR, \fB\-v\fR
Display version number and exit.
.SH CONFIG
Place a \fB.whiterose.toml\fR in the repository root to customize
behavior:
.RS
.PP
.nf
protected_branches = ["main", "master"]
auto_upstream = true
smart_pull = true
novice_mode = false
backup_on_destructive = true
.fi
.RE
.SH ALIASES
.TP
\fBnew\-branch <name>\fR
git checkout \-b <name>
.TP
\fBswitch <name>\fR
git checkout <name>
.TP
\fBsave\fR [\-m <msg>]
git add \-A && git commit (prompts if no \-m)
.TP
\fBsync\fR
git pull
.TP
\fBshare\fR
git push
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI~/.whiterose_history\fR
Command history persisted across sessions.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The shell uses file descriptor 3 internally for cwd tracking.
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at \fBhttps://github.com/SodiqovSardor/WhiteRose/issues\fR.
